The paper deals with coding theory and specifically focuses on the Euclidean hulls of MDS codes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves algebraic geometry and combinatorics, which are relevant to sub-categories cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses computational methods to determine the dimensions of Euclidean hulls, which could fall under sub-categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
